<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1172101685033">
<term>missing order</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172101793056">interference maximum that is not seen because it coincides with a diffraction minimum</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172101790165">
<term>two-slit diffraction pattern</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172102105173">diffraction pattern of two slits of width <emphasis effect="italics">D</emphasis> that are separated by a distance <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> is the interference pattern of two point sources separated by <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> multiplied by the diffraction pattern of a slit of width <emphasis effect="italics">D</emphasis></meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>


